title: Killing of Alex Pretti by immigration agents fuels anger in traumatized Minneapolis
subhed: Two weeks after the death of Renee Good, Alex Pretti, a 37-year-old nurse, was killed during a confrontation between Border Patrol officers and residents in Minneapolis. Democrats are now threatening to block funding for the Department of Homeland Security, even if it means triggering another government shutdown.
byline: By Nicolas Chapuis (New York (United States) correspondent)

title: Pressure on Trump intensifies after ICE kills a second US citizen
Russia steps up attacks on Ukraine's shipping routes in the Black Sea
Why the Israeli army doubts Hamas can be demilitarized
subhed: The second phase of Donald Trump's 'peace plan' for Gaza calls for the disarmament of the Islamist group. However, Israeli security leaders are convinced that it will continue to maneuver in order to maintain its capacity for both military and terrorist action.

title: 'The MAGA movement is divided in the face of Trump's openly imperial ambitions'
subhed: A significant segment of Donald Trump's supporters is in favor of isolationism. However, most of them would continue to follow the American president as long as he retains the backing of evangelical conservatives, political scientist Thomas Charrayre writes.

title: Paris Men's Fashion Week: Véronique Nichanian delivers final lesson in elegance at Hermès
subhed: After 38 years leading menswear for the luxury house, the artistic director presented a final collection that was easy to wear and crafted from sumptuous materials, with leather taking center stage throughout.

title: The dangerous liaisons of French rapper Koba LaD
subhed: At 25, Koba LaD, whose real name is Marcel Loutarila, is one of the leading names in French rap. He is suspected by the courts of having financially supported the escape of drug trafficker Mohamed Amra after his deadly prison break in May 2024. At the center of the investigation is the Black Manjak Family, a murky group formed around the artist.

title: Inside the workshop where dress forms are made

France is considering banning phones in high schools. This school near Paris already does.
subhed: The Lycée Michelet, a large school complex with 2,300 students, banned mobile phones in its hallways in April 2025. School officials report positive results from a decision made in agreement with the entire educational community.

title: Generative AI, psychiatry and the risks of self-service therapy
subhed: Millions of people use chatbots like ChatGPT to share their distress, and the scientific community has warned about the risks vulnerable people face. Generative AI has shaken up psychiatric consultations, fueled tech giants' ambitions and emerged as a credible tool for analyzing pathologies.

title: How surveillance companies track smartphone users through advertising data
subhed: Companies are offering law enforcement agencies the ability to track smartphone users through advertising data gathered on their devices. Le Monde attended confidential presentations of these new surveillance tools to learn more.
